
Overview of noun crook

The noun crook has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) criminal, felon, crook, outlaw, malefactor -- (someone who has committed a crime or has been legally convicted of a crime)
2. (1) bend, crook, twist, turn -- (a circular segment of a curve; "a bend in the road"; "a crook in the path")
3. crook, shepherd's crook -- (a long staff with one end being hook shaped)

